HEADWORD: Excursive
<hw>Ex*cur"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Prone to make
excursions; wandering; roving; exploring; <as>as, an <ex>excursive</ex>
fancy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The course of <qex>excursive</qex> . . . understandings.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ex*cur"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ex*cur"sive*ness</wf>, , <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excursus</ent>⟦br⟧
